<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n09148o"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09148o">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09148o"> 148(o)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> living stone</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Re Harry Johnston&apos;s biography of Livingstone]</font> When <cite>Punch</cite> punned his historic pun he little guessed what a double-barrelled thing he made of it: <br>&ldquo;<i>He needs no epitaph to guard a name, <br>Which men shall prize while worthy work is known; <br>He lived and died for good be that his fame, <br>Let marble crumble: this is <mark>LIVING-STONE</mark>.</i>&rdquo; <p>For Livingstone&apos;s African tombstone was no mere crumbling marble but a stately tree, a literal living-&ldquo;stone.&rdquo;</p> <small> Dan Crawford, <a name="BTLG1" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BTLG1"><cite title="source">Back to the Long Grass</cite></a> (1923) 76-77</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
